used on sponsor side leveraged finance) - supported by a deep bench of associates. A steady flow of high-value instructions from blue-chip clients and an ever-expanding international footprint create a dynamic environment in which first-rate business development support is integral to the success of the practice.\n\nROLE PURPOSE\n\nThis role leads business development support for the lender side of our Debt Finance practice (19 partners), and supports and supervises business development (led by a colleague) for the fund finance and trade & commodity finance (TCF) product lines.\nIts aim is to design and drive initiatives to deepen client relationships, expand wallet share with existing sponsors and their designated lenders/bond underwriters, generate new mandates from target arranger, underwriter and direct-lending institutions, and enhance the firm’s market profile in the leveraged finance, fund finance and TCF markets.\nThe role holder should have a good understanding of the market, the products and the clients in these spaces, and be a credible voice both internally and externally.\n\nROLE & RESPONSIBILITIES\n\nStrategy and planning\nWork closely with the partners and other team members to design and implement the business development strategy for the lender side leveraged finance practice.\nPlay a key influencing role in partner meetings, bring ideas forward and implement and execute projects.\nSupport and supervise business development activity in relation to the fund finance and TCF product lines.\nLiaise with the business development manager responsible for the sponsor side of the practice and act as a conduit for sharing information and facilitating coordinated strategy across the two sides of the Debt Finance practice where appropriate.\n\nClient relationship management\n\nAssist partners and other team members in coordinating client targeting efforts including by coordinating relationship teams within debt finance made up of partners and associates and convening and leading in client focussed team meetings.\nClient relationship management responsibility for a small number of private credit clients and/or designating financial sponsors, working on specific client tactics for those clients, including for example secondee debriefs, client listening processes and the follow up from them, presentations and training, etc.\nDevelop knowledge of the key existing and prospective clients. Ensure regular sharing of information on client activities.\nLiaise with the business development manager responsible for the sponsor side of the practice in order to stay informed and facilitate any joint opportunities for engagement\n\nMarket, product and client research\n\nOversee a flow of market, product and client intelligence (e.g. pipeline deals, marquee deals, major players, market shares, key client contact moves and developments) to partners and associates. Work with the research team on regular market overview output.\nMonitor BD diary to identify upcoming client meetings and ensure partners are briefed before those meetings.\n\nEvents and hospitality\n\nLead the strategy for identifying campaigns, events, and hospitality initiatives to raise the firm’s profile and deepen client engagement within the leveraged finance market, working with the relevant central teams as appropriate.\nLead the strategy for identifying appropriate targeted event sponsorships.\nAdvise on best use of hospitality opportunities and monitor marketing budget spend, liaise with leadership team re authorisation of significant spend.\nTrack marketing spend against clients and individuals/teams within clients to ensure activities are aligned with overall strategic priorities.\nEstablish clear objectives and measurement frameworks for all campaigns, events and sponsorships to assess effectiveness, pipeline impact, and brand enhancement, integrating lessons learned into future activities.\n\nCampaigns and profile raising\n\nWork with fee earners and the knowledge